description: Recently sold: $263,000.

Recently sold: $188,500. Stunning town home on a quiet street is a marvelous space. Features: bamboo flooring, 12 feet height at entry with unique glass and wood railing for living room and stairs; open concept living and dining room; breakfast bar seating at kitchen. Great space for gatherings and family functions. Dappled evening light on the deck provides space for outdoor dining with stairs to ground for your grilling station. Association center courtyard is large with mature trees and green space. Morning light filters through clerestory entry window and can cast rainbows across living room. Lower level has family room with gas fireplace, an office and bath. Egress windows would allow for a third bedroom use downstairs. Easy access to Hwys 52, 62, I-94 and I-494. 20 minutes to airport. Shopping is plentiful on nearby Robert Street. Parks and walking trails nearby include Mississippi Riverwalk, Kaposia Frisbee Golf Park, Thompson Park and more. Small town feel in the metro area is a blessing you'll enjoy.

Perfect for a family/entertainment area. Great home for any size family.

description:
Recently sold: $215,000. Cute, bright, & affordable! Don't be fooled by the front curb appeal, this 1,496 square-foot house has more room than you might think. Enjoy living comfortably in this clean 3-bedroom 2-bathroom home without having to break the bank to get it. 

You'll love cooking meals in the huge updated kitchen, the 2 updated bathrooms, open floor plan on the main level, hardwood floors, all newer windows, and tasteful updates throughout. The finished lower level is perfect for watching movies or having family game nights, where there's also a good-sized bedroom and 3/4 bath. You'll love sitting on your sunny back deck watching the kids play in the large fenced yard during the day, and around the firepit in the evenings.

The home is in quiet residential South St. Paul, with close access to 494 and Hwy 52 to get all around the cities. Kaposia Elementary is within walking distance, Spruce Park is 2 blocks away, and Gerten's is a short drive.

Whether you're looking for that affordable family nest with the chef's kitchen you've been dreaming of, or a one-level home with a short 10-minute commute to Downtown St Paul, this fabulous stucco rambler is just the ticket. Don't wait on this!

description:
Recently sold: $257,000. A beautiful two story home located in a quiet neighborhood, sitting high on a bluff overlooking the river.

Spacious light-filled living room, with pretty details, including coved ceiling and see-through wood-burningfireplace. The other side of the fireplace is in the den, with a floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace face and built-in shelves to one side. Lots of windows in theden, and gleaming hardwood floors.

The formal dining room also has acoved ceiling. Large window overlooking the back yard. Grids on all thewindows in the home, except the porch.

Spacious kitchen, with lots of cabinet and counter top space, including a pantry. Eat-in ktichen, with room for an informal dining set. Door opens to the porch.

Great porch! Baseboard heat and a ceiling fan make this comfortable no matter what the weather! Windows all around to let in natural light. Knotty pine walls, plushardwood floors. The back door allows access from thedetached garage. There is a large coat closet, plus a convenient built-in bench by the door.

All three bedrooms are on the upper level, along with an office and a full bath. All three bedrooms have ceiling fans. This home has plenty of natural light, including from a window at thetop of the staircase. Upper level hall is wide, and large enough for extra decor.

The lower level features a finished family room, with another floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace. There is a door on one side of the fireplace, that leads to a small room that can be used as an office, workroom, or for storage. There is a storage closet off this room. Lots and lots of storage space in this home -- there is also extra space in theutility room (off the laundry) for storage, plus large storage closets off the family room and laundry. The lower level 3/4 bath includes a linen closet. The laundry room has a double utility sink.

The back yard is enclosed with a privacy fence. Flat yard, with open space in the middle -- good for activities! The 2-car garage is off an alley, and has extra parking space.

There is a peek-a-boo view of the river from thefront yard.

Directions 12th Ave to Congress, East to Stewart, North to Home
